# DashTab Frontend — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Context
Restaurant operating system (POS, payments, inventory, analytics). Next.js 15 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind. All pages currently use mock data — no real API calls yet.

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router, Server Components by default)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS + `tailwind-merge` + `clsx`
- Radix UI primitives + Lucide icons
- `react-hook-form` for forms
- `sonner` for toasts, `next-themes` for theming
- `recharts` for charts

## File & Folder Conventions
- Path alias `@/` maps to `src/frontend/` — always use it for internal imports
- Components go in `components/` as plain `.tsx` files, no barrel `index.ts` files
- Custom hooks go in `hooks/`, API clients and utilities in `lib/`, shared types in `types/`
- Page files live under `app/` following Next.js App Router conventions

## Components
- Default to React Server Components; add `"use client"` only when you need interactivity or browser APIs
- Props use TypeScript `interface`, not `type`, unless a union is needed
- Variants and sizes use prop unions (`variant: "primary" | "secondary"`), not CVA
- Never use inline styles or CSS modules — Tailwind only
- Class names: `cn(...)` from `@/lib/utils` (uses `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`)

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore` without a comment explaining why
- Define shared data shapes in `types/` and import from there
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` for external/API data, then narrow with Zod when validation is added

## Forms
- Use `react-hook-form` for all form state — no raw `useState` for form fields
- Validate with Zod schemas (resolver: `@hookform/resolvers/zod`) when Zod is added
- Show inline field errors below each input using `formState.errors`
- File inputs: controlled via RHF `Controller`, never uncontrolled

## State Management (target state — not yet wired)
- Server state: TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) — wrap pages in `QueryClientProvider`
- Client/UI state: Zustand stores in `lib/store/`
- No prop drilling beyond 2 levels — lift to Zustand or query cache

## Data Fetching
- Currently all pages use mock data — when replacing, put fetch logic in `lib/api/` modules
- Server Components fetch directly (no useEffect); Client Components use TanStack Query
- Never fetch in `useEffect` for data that belongs in the query cache

## Styling
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use `@tailwindcss/container-queries` (`@container`) for component-level responsiveness
- Dark mode via `next-themes` — use `dark:` variants, never hardcode colors

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-reachable (`tabIndex`, `onKeyDown` where needed)
- Use Radix UI primitives (Dialog, DropdownMenu, etc.) for complex widgets — they handle a11y
- Every `<img>` needs a meaningful `alt`; decorative images use `alt=""`
- Form inputs must have associated `<label>` (via `htmlFor`) or `aria-label`
- Use semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`

## Performance
- Use `next/dynamic` with `{ ssr: false }` for heavy client-only components (charts, rich editors)
- Images: always `next/image` with explicit `width`/`height` or `fill`
- Keep page-level JS bundles lean — check with `@next/bundle-analyzer` before merging large deps

## Testing (target — not yet configured)
- Unit tests: Jest + React Testing Library in `tests/frontend/`
- File naming: `ComponentName.test.tsx` co-located or under `tests/frontend/`
- Test behavior, not implementation — query by role/label, not by class name
- e2e: Playwright for critical flows (auth, place order)

## Do Not
- Do not use `pages/` router — this project uses App Router only
- Do not install a second CSS framework or component library alongside Tailwind/Radix
- Do not commit mock data as permanent fixtures — it lives in page files until API is wired
- Do not add `console.log` statements in committed code
- Do not use `export default` for anything except Next.js page/layout files
